I wanted to like the bed and at first it worked great, it fit perfectly in my dogs crate and he seemed to be comfortable enough with it. HOWEVER, it sheds like CRAZY! I had read a review talking about that, but I decided to buy it anyways cus it could’ve just been their bed. Turns out it’s mine too. Every single day I would have to vacuum inside and around on the outside of his crate because the fur balls that would come off the bed were so much that they would get carried out around the living room (where the crates at) by the normal inside air. It was so annoying. Not to mention my dog has allergies and the amount of fur that came off the bed was very uncomfortable for him to the point he couldn’t sleep in his crate with that bed. It was a problem for me because his crate doesn’t have a base (it was a hand-me-down crate) so the bed had to be there or he would be even more uncomfortable. Anyway, point is this bed although seemed to work for the price, now has to been thrown away because it is completely useless to me and no amount of vacuuming stops the fur from coming off. I imagine the bed would have to be furless for that to happen. So waste of money there.

There was some extra leg length that bunches up some but not bad. They’re extremely soft. They hid my pouch pretty well. I can also lift my legs high and squat with no feeling of gaining tightness on my legs or anywhere. So they are pretty stretchy as well. I’m happy with them.

This is the perfect beach towel! I wanted something large enough to fit me, my husband, and my young daughter comfortably, along with all of our beach gear that we want to protect from sand. It comes with stakes and packets to fill with sand to weigh it down, which is great so I don’t have to worry about putting something in each corner. I also intend to use this inside our beach tent to make it more waterproof. It’s light weight and small when packed up. A must-have for every beachgoer.
aspect: large enough to fit family and beach gear comfortably

I wore these for a 24hr adventure race and was pleased. I was worried my backside would get overly sore with 90+ miles of biking but faired no worse than I’d expect to in fully padded bike shorts. They held up well over 30+ miles of trekking in that race with no chaffing or discomfort. I did wear UA boxer briefs underneath as I could feel the seam of the pad against my skin without them and didn’t want to risk irritation over that distance.

This comforter was an easy wash and dried up great (especially since I had to re wash it after forgetting in the washer ????)! Looks and feels great! Was originally going to be a spare but it’s in my regular rotations now, when my kids aren’t trying to take it! I’m hoping they come out with more prints but if not, might just have to pick up another one.

Needed a new microwave  bought this one and right away I noticed how it doesn't make a lot of noise while operating and you can turn off the "beeping when finished " feature so you don't have to hear that either. It has a metal-like looking door which goes well with stainless steel appliances. It has a sensor pad built in that I have used to cook potatoes so it knows how long to cook them you can use it for other foods too. It comes with a great operating manual, actually 2 speperate ones -in English and one in Spanish. I'm still learning all the bells and whistles but I'm very pleased with my purchase.

reviewBody: Okay, so let's nip this in the bud. The people who left bad reviews because their "sound stage changed" and "it sounds like X, Y, and also Z!" - take it with a grain of salt. There's a few reasons for this. First and foremost... duh. It's like moving your speaker that was 2 feet away and surrounded in concrete, to 4 feet away and surrounded in wood. Anyone who orders these thinking the sound will not change shouldn't be writing clarity-centric reviews trying to sound like an audiophile. Because an audiophile wouldn't even get these. Master Technicians don't get Harbor Freight tools, they get Snap-On.

reviewTitle: Good alternative for discontinued IKEA Ektorp sofa covers.

While I prefer the feel of cotton, the polyester isn't too bad. Overall, I have to say that I'm pretty impressed & would order from this company again.

reviewTitle: Not entirely leather on the outside!
reviewBody: Description says this is a leather bag and/or I missed the part about the non-leather slide pocket?? To me, this looks far different in person than it did in the pictures and the video in the listing. It’s not attractive at all, and I’m going to return it. I initially thought I’d accidentally gotten a fake but then noticed others reporting this in their reviews.  I guess I should have read them first, but the reason I didn’t was because I had bought a really similar bag from this company in the past; thus, I may not have been discerning enough in reading about this one. Either way, the difference in materials is not the look for me, especially given the price I paid.

When it comes to ladder safety these are worth every penny vs having a ladder fall.

I love this kind of popcorn and I decided to give the bowl a try. The butter does not distribute evenly over all the popcorn (in all 12 buckets) and there’s extreme amount of salt. You’ll be satisfied at first with its buttery taste but as you get further down into the bowl there’s hardly any flavor. You also have to be on top of when it finishes popping or else the bottom of the bucket gets burnt and you risk burning your popcorn. In my opinion you got more flavor distributed in the single serving bags.

reviewTitle: Best for speech, sturdy, comfy, calls so so.
reviewBody: As other stated the bass sounds are reduced for music, but works terrific for podcasts etc. The power on power off volume cannot be adjusted and should be turned on or off we’re not attached to your ears. It is very very loud. It is easy to have these headphones too loud when trying to override exterior noises, like on a bus or around other’s loud speech. This could result in tinnitus. However they are terrific for listening to things at low-volume without disturbing others, in bed, while they are on phone, etc. Voice to speech text does not work well with this, and background noises are amplified for persons receiving your phone call. This being said the value for money and comfort is hard to beat. It does not have a volume adjustment on the headset, but this can be completed by pushing them further forward from the years to reduce sound or slid back closer to the year to make the volume louder.  These seem very sturdy, long battery life. I have a small head and sensitive este, these don’t hurt me, very comfortable, leaves enough room behind my head to insert a forefinger yet ride well during activity.  I can also wear sunglasses with them, or one earpiece for two way radio and still get good benefit from the headphones.

However they are terrific for listening to things at low-volume without disturbing others, in bed, while they are on phone, etc. Voice to speech text does not work well with this, and background noises are amplified for persons receiving your phone call. This being said the value for money and comfort is hard to beat. It does not have a volume adjustment on the headset, but this can be completed by pushing them further forward from the years to reduce sound or slid back closer to the year to make the volume louder.  These seem very sturdy, long battery life. I have a small head and sensitive este, these don’t hurt me, very comfortable, leaves enough room behind my head to insert a forefinger yet ride well during activity.  I can also wear sunglasses with them, or one earpiece for two way radio and still get good benefit from the headphones.

reviewTitle: Size down if you want a snug fit
reviewBody: I’m 5’2, 125lb and wear a size 2, about a 27in waist. I usually get a medium in tight workout shorts but they swallowed me. I exchanged for a small and it was much better but I think the XS would fit me perfectly. If you like a more snug fit, definitely size down. Now that I have the right size I really like these and will be ordering more. Buttery soft, comfortable and super high waisted.

reviewTitle: Excellent Steam Mop, Easy to Use
reviewBody: We bought this mop after something oil based got on our tiled kitchen floor while we were moving and we were having trouble cleaning it. We found this steam mop, ordered it & it arrived quickly and did the trick. The floor looked great & it did not take a lot of time. It is lightweight & very easy to use.  Compact, so uses minimal storage space. We were very pleased with the job it did & thrilled it reduced the time we spent getting our house ready to sell. I would definitely recommend this product.

I suppose I should have been more suspicious about a mattress cover that claimed to be both breathable and water-proof. The inside of it is lined with some sort of plastic or rubber, which may be waterproof, but is not breathable. You can test this yourself, put it against your lips and blow. No air passes through. There's a softer fabric over the top, but that's not going to provide any sort of air flow. If you have a mattress that's supposed to be breathable or have a cooling effect, a sheet of plastic between you and it pretty much nullifies the effect.

While I do like the pattern, they are on the smaller side and the draw string is way to short. I ordered a XXL and the string to tighten the shorts should of been 59" for that size. As it was, I measured mine at 55" and couldn't even tie a bow this when you put the shorts on, the string pulls inside the string hole this making it very difficult to pull back out. That's a key component this why I knocked 3 stars off. Had to buy 2 64" draw strings at $12 just to be able to tie an appropriate not so pants stay up.

reviewTitle: We Needed More Memory than 8 gig
reviewBody: We had an 8 gig SD Card that was not enough, so we ordered this 32 gig. We have had it for a couple of weeks. We turned off  the phone, took out the battery, replaced the SD card, plugged in the battery, turned on the phone. We took a pictures, used the phone. Everything seemed to work as before. I looked at the storage. There are 29.xx gigs still available on the SD. Everything seems to work well. It is nice to have some available memory on my phone again. When we find my wife's phone we will order another one.

Great scrub pants. I’m an ER RN. The scrubs get a good work out for many shifts during their lifetime. ( last about 2 years)..1 wash a week. They fit really well, there’s plenty of room in them, and they’re very colorfast in the wash. They have cargo pockets on each leg, regular front pockets, and a pocket on the back for your wallet with a button on it. I love the design. It’s the only one I will buy now. Would buy them again. Thank you.

reviewTitle: Impressive can and you don’t have to worry about The lid smacking into your counter
reviewBody: Impressive can, and you don’t have to worry about the lid smacking into your countertop as our old one did, the only downside to this can is that it is a little bit short for me, as I am a 6 foot tall person and when I reach down full extension of my arm I still have to bend down another four or 5 inches to trigger the Cans sensor and I do have a pretty long arms, so if they can was four or 5 inches taller I think it would be a little bit of an improvement. Not a fault of the can just for me it would be ideal if it was a few inches taller maybe a slightly higher base or something?

reviewTitle: Worked wonders for my spraned ankle.
reviewBody: I had broken a small bone on the top of my foot when the tendon snapped up. Also tore a ligament on the side of the ankle. Was in a boot for two months and the swelling and pain continued. This stopped the severe swelling in my ankle and foot I had been having for over two months. The healing process seemed to speed up after wearing this each day. Happy I bought this.

Got unit today, works perfectly. I initially used my Zone 2 out rca connectors, but not all sources routed out. Instead, I am using the headphone adapter into the 1/8th" input. It would have been helpful if they had a 1/4" headphone adapter but it's 2021 and I had one in my electronic archives. (we all have those boxes don't we?). Anyway, latency and quality was similar with HD or LL switch so not sure what the big deal is with that - sounds great. Good headroom, and can use volume on receiver to set level. Watched 30 min of Almost Famous and it never cut out. I got them so I could use the treadmill and watch movies without blasting the house away. perfect.

The ZesGood-battery box finally offered me a means of organizing our household batteries. The case easily stands on our shelf. Inside the case are multiple foam spots for inserting batteries of various sizes. Because we had so many AA batteries, we could even use the AAA spots to insert the AA’s.  The foam design is the key to making this battery organizer genius. I also like the zip pocket on the inside cover that allows me to store the battery tester (comes with bag) along with a plethora of flat, button types of batteries.

reviewTitle: Excellent Sea Salt Packaged in Convenient Cardboard Containers
reviewBody: The Morton All Purpose Sea Salt is a good quality salt to season all your favorite dishes with.  The salt is pretty much preground sea salt with no iodide.  It’s flavor is sound, the ground is fairly uniform, and the container is perfect for bringing to picnics and family gatherings as it’s disposable.  If you absolutely hate the look of the container, it’s easy enough to pour the salt into a prettier dispenser using the large opening at the top of the container, and each 4.4 ounce container is about the right size for fill most salt dispensers.  With 12 containers of salt per pack, you’ll have plenty of salt to season all your entrees.

reviewTitle: Cheap table. Defective parts that they refused to replace. They told me to drill the holes myself.
reviewBody: The white faux marble is less than an inch thick and looks really cheap. The legs had the holes on the wrong side so I couldn't complete assembly. The bottom bar that connects stabilizes the table and because the holes where on the wrong side I couldn't install that bar causing the table to be uneven and unstable. I messaged the seller twice and they told me to drill the holes myself and that they couldn't send me correct replacement legs. I'm really disappointed. SAVE YOUR MONEY

reviewTitle: Not a perfect fit but it works well and costs 1/3 of the OEM part
reviewBody: I replaced the original light on our 2012 Armada with this assembly. No issues getting everything hooked up, it's just a pain to get to the light. I actually liked that it didn't come with any pigtails for anything, so I just disconnected everything from the old light after I removed it from the spoiler. I didn't have to run anything back through the liftgate. The fit is not 100% perfect, as the gap at the edge between the light and the cutout in the spoiler is slightly larger than it needs to be. It's not noticeably off, though. Hard to knock it for the price - $40 plus tax. Cheapest I could find from Nissan was about $123. Next cheapest is Dorman for $90.

Rich, creamy & sweet. I got addicted to Carnation malted milk powder while I was on house arrest during Covid. My favourite way to eat it is sprinkled over vanilla ice cream with peanut butter, squished together with my spoon. Almost any milkshake is better with malt, especially carmel or butterscotch. Try it for yourself and you'll understand why everyone over a certain age used to talk about going to the drive in and  drinking malts. SMART GENERATION!!!
